I now have a thorough understanding of the entire codebase. Let me present the complete implementation plan.

---

## Detailed Implementation Plan: Differentiated Laboratories for K3rn.Labs

---

### 1. Architecture Overview

The plan involves 10 files: 4 modified and 6 new. Implementation follows a bottom-up dependency order: shared hook first, then API route, then lab-specific components, then page orchestrators, then shared component updates.

**Key architectural insight from codebase exploration:** The `saveProjectToStorage()` function in `analysis-results.tsx` (line 167-200) saves projects to `localStorage` under key `k3rn_active_project`, and the workspace page (line 58-98) merges them into the `k3rn_projects` array. The stored project shape includes `id`, `title`, `text`, `description`, `globalScore`, `recommendation`, `confidenceLevel`, `analysis` (with `axes`, `synthesis`, `risks`), `timestamp`, `isDemo`, and critically `fullResult` which is the complete `AnalysisOutput` object. This `fullResult` field is the primary data source for the labs.

**Data shape of a stored project (from `analysis-results.tsx` lines 178-199):**
```typescript
{
  id: string;                          // result.idea.idea_id
  title: string;                       // max 60 chars
  text: string;                        // full input text
  description: string;                 // result.idea.raw_summary
  globalScore: number;                 // result.scores.global_score
  recommendation: 'GO'|'EXPLORE'|'PARK'|'KILL';
  confidenceLevel: 'LOW'|'MEDIUM'|'HIGH';
  analysis: {
    axes: { label: string; score: number; justification: string }[];
    synthesis: string;                 // result.decision.summary
    risks: string[];                   // result.risks mapped to descriptions
  };
  timestamp: string;
  isDemo: boolean;
  fullResult: AnalysisOutput;          // complete canonical output
}
```

The `fullResult` contains the typed `AnalysisOutput` with `risks` (array of `{ axis, description, severity }`), `levers` (array of `{ axis, action, expected_impact }`), `decision`, `scores`, and `analysis` (with full `AxisAnalysis` objects including `blocking_gap`).

---

### 2. Implementation Order and File Details

---

#### STEP 1: `src/hooks/use-project.ts` (NEW)

**Purpose:** Shared hook to load a project by ID from localStorage.

**Dependencies:** None (foundational)

**Detailed specification:**

```typescript
// src/hooks/use-project.ts
"use client";

import { useState, useEffect } from "react";
import type { AnalysisOutput } from "@/lib/analysis/types";

// Mirror the shape saved by analysis-results.tsx saveProjectToStorage()
export interface StoredProject {
  id: string;
  title: string;
  text: string;
  description: string;
  globalScore: number;
  recommendation: "GO" | "EXPLORE" | "PARK" | "KILL";
  confidenceLevel: "LOW" | "MEDIUM" | "HIGH";
  analysis: {
    axes: { label: string; score: number; justification: string }[];
    synthesis: string;
    risks: string[];
  };
  timestamp: string;
  isDemo?: boolean;
  fullResult?: AnalysisOutput;
}

export function useProject(id: string) {
  const [project, setProject] = useState<StoredProject | null>(null);
  const [isLoading, setIsLoading] = useState(true);

  useEffect(() => {
    if (typeof window === "undefined" || !id) {
      setIsLoading(false);
      return;
    }

    // 1. Try k3rn_projects array first (primary source)
    const storedProjects = JSON.parse(
      localStorage.getItem("k3rn_projects") || "[]"
    );
    const found = storedProjects.find((p: any) => p.id === id);

    if (found) {
      setProject(found as StoredProject);
      setIsLoading(false);
      return;
    }

    // 2. Fallback: check k3rn_active_project
    const activeProject = localStorage.getItem("k3rn_active_project");
    if (activeProject) {
      const parsed = JSON.parse(activeProject);
      if (parsed.id === id) {
        setProject(parsed as StoredProject);
        setIsLoading(false);
        return;
      }
    }

    // 3. Not found
    setIsLoading(false);
  }, [id]);

  return { project, isLoading };
}
```

**Key considerations:**
- The hook searches both `k3rn_projects` (the array, primary source) and `k3rn_active_project` (fallback for projects just analyzed but not yet merged).
- The `StoredProject` interface mirrors exactly what `saveProjectToStorage()` creates in `analysis-results.tsx`.
- The `fullResult` field is optional because older mock projects (lines 87-93 of workspace page) do not have it.

